text: Cosmioconcha dedonderi is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae, the dove snails. ==Description== The length of the shell attains 9 mm. ==Distribution== This species occurs in the Caribbean Sea off Panama. ==References== * Monsecour, K. & Monsecour, D., 2006. Two new Cosmioconcha (Gastropoda: Neogastropoda: Columbellidae) from the Caribbean. Gloria Maris 45(1-2): 7-13 ==External links== * Category:Columbellidae Category:Gastropods described in 2006
title: Cosmioconcha dedonderi
